    "summary": "One strand of my research focuses on the dynamics of emulation between countries that identify as belonging to the Global South; I am particularly interested in understanding under what circumstances development lessons are transferred between locales in East Asia and Africa. For example, I have recently completed some research on the transfer of Japanese productivity methods (kaizen) to Ethiopian workplaces.\n\nI am also a researcher on the 3WE project (Wellbeing, Women and Work in Ethiopia), which looks at the wellbeing of Ethiopian women in the country's export-oriented horticultural and apparel sectors. Further information can be found at http://3we.nl/.  \n\nI teach several courses at the BA and MA levels that focus on globalisation, international development and global value chains, and supervise several PhD dissertations.\n\nMy findings have been featured in The Guardian, Jeune Afrique and CCTV America; my academic publications can be found at http://bit.ly/1fBfbLx.",
